Surveillance cameras caught the thief taking $9,000 out of the account of Kate Sullivan at Chase branches in Commack and Freeport on September 23 . 
  State police say the female suspect then racked up $4,000 in bills after opening four store credit cards in Sullivan's name in New Haven . 
  Sullivan had lung cancer and was informed of the fraud while fighting for her life at Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center  . 
  She died five days later . 
  The 50-year-old had worked as a marketing executive for fashion designers . 
 